[1] North Carolina (Buncombe County): beaver, human exposure
Date: Mon 11 Jul 2016
Source: WLOS News 13, Asheville NC [edited]
http://wlos.com/news/local/woman-bit-by-beaver-at-beaver-lake


A local woman is undergoing rabies treatment after she was bitten by a beaver last week [week of 4 Jul 2016].

The 67-year-old woman was paddleboarding on Beaver Lake [Asheville, North Carolina] on [Fri 8 Jul 2016] at the time of the bite. She was taken to Mission for emergency treatment.

Police say the beaver was caught a day later and euthanized.

Results for the rabies test from the Western Veterinary Diagnostic Lab will be returned on [Tue 12 Jul 2016], and the warden says Lake View Park is closed until further notice.

The warden reminds residents that seeing a beaver in the middle of the day is not normal and you should stay away from one if seen.

[Byline: Krystyna Biassou]

